# Rasm Reference Docs

Read `.claude/skills/docgen/SKILL.md`, `.claude/skills/style-standards/SKILL.md`, and root `AGENTS.md` §5.

## Sources

- Treat checked-in API docs, local XML, decompile output, manifest files, and runnable tool output as stronger evidence than public examples.
- Use current official documentation only when repo-owned evidence does not cover the API.
- Keep source dates, package versions, host locations, and command outputs explicit when they are part of the claim.

## Scope

- `docs/system-api-map` owns BCL, `System.*`, host references, package policy, and SDK/runtime surface.
- `docs/external-libs` owns approved product library APIs such as LanguageExt, Thinktecture, MathNet, RhinoCommon, GH2, and Eto.
- `docs/testing-libs` owns xUnit v3, CsCheck, Verify, ArchUnitNET, coverlet, Stryker, BenchmarkDotNet, SharpFuzz, and bridge test APIs.
- `docs/usage.md` owns the cross-stack implementation source-order ladder.
- `docs/host` owns RhinoCommon and GH2 native SDK boundaries.
- `docs/host-libraries.md` owns composition-root package adoption (not-in-graph until consumer).

## Rules

- Remove stale commands, unsupported platforms, invented package names, and unverified compatibility claims.
- Do not document workarounds that bypass central package management, app-bundle host references, or the bridge operator.
- Keep examples compilable or mark them as schematic only when they cannot be run in repo tooling.
